  "text": "Secondly, the remaining unsubstituted position can be either on the aldehyde form (structure 2-3 in Figure 1 ), or in the reduced form due to partial carbonyl reduction by picoline borane as described above (structure 4-5 in Figure 1 ). Partial carbonyl reduction is also supported by structural analysis by NMR [CITATION_1] . Thirdly, residual (unreduced) carbonyl functionalities could also be on the form of hemiacetals.",
